The paper deals with spectral sparsification of hypergraphs, which is a topic related to graph algorithms and spectral graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves machine learning and optimization, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves geometric algorithms and computational geometry, which are related to cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
